# VS Code extensions installed by modules/90-vscode.sh.
#
# One extension ID per line, in publisher.name form. Blank lines and lines
# starting with # are ignored. Find an extension's ID on its Marketplace page
# under "More Info", or run `code --list-extensions` to dump what you already
# have installed.
#
# Starts empty on purpose — same reasoning as dev-packages.list. Add what you
# actually reach for, commit, and re-run install.sh. Installs are idempotent,
# so re-running never duplicates or downgrades anything.
#
# For example:
#   ms-python.python
#   ms-azuretools.vscode-docker
#   esbenp.prettier-vscode
